#. Tag: title
#: browsing.docbook:10
#, no-c-format
msgid "Browsing"
msgstr "Brskanje"

#. Tag: para
#: browsing.docbook:11
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Once you have annotated your images and videos, &kphotoalbum; is ready to "
"let you browse through your images. If you compare that to <xref linkend="
"\"fig-empty-browser-window\"/> , you will see that there now is items "
"available in each of the categories for <literal>People</literal>, "
"<literal>Places</literal>, and <literal>Keywords</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Ko ste slike in videoposnetke označili z opombami, vam &kphotoalbum; omogoča "
"brskanje po slikah. Če to primerjate z <xref linkend=\"fig-empty-browser-"
"window\"/>, boste videli, da so zdaj v vsaki od kategorij na voljo elementi "
"za <literal>Ljudje</literal>, <literal>Kraji</literal> in <literal>Ključne "
"besede</literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: browsing.docbook:17
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the browser window you can see the categories you typed information into "
"when annotating your images and videos. In addition there are items for "
"searching based on EXIF information on images, browsing the folder structure "
"of your hard disk, and of course showing the actual thumbnails. Lets "
"describe each item in turn."
msgstr ""
"V oknu brskalnika si lahko ogledate kategorije, v katere ste vnesli podatke, "
"ko ste dodajali opombe k svojim slikam in videoposnetkom. Poleg tega "
"obstajajo elementi za iskanje na podlagi informacij EXIF na slikah, brskanje "
"po strukturi map na vašem trdem disku in seveda prikazovanje dejanskih "
"sličic. Opišimo vsako postavko po vrsti."

#. Tag: para
#: browsing.docbook:23
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Pressing the mouse on <literal>People</literal>, the browser window will "
"change, as you can see in <xref linkend=\"fig-browser-for-persons\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Če pritisnete miško na <literal>Ljudje</literal>, se okno brskalnika "
"spremeni, kot lahko vidite v <xref linkend=\"fig-browser-for-persons\"/>."

#. Tag: title
#: browsing.docbook:28
#, no-c-format
msgid "Browser window when People was selected."
msgstr "Okno brskalnika, ko so bili izbrani Ljudje."

#. Tag: para
#: browsing.docbook:37
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The browser is now populated with the people you specified for your images "
"and videos <footnote><para>You may notice that the item <literal>Pets</"
"literal> has a special icon. For details about that, see <xref linkend=\"sec-"
"specifying-categories\"/>.</para></footnote>, selecting a person will bring "
"you back to the original state for the browser. This time, however, we are "
"<emphasis>in the scope</emphasis> of the person we selected. That means that "
"we only show information about images and videos containing that person. See "
"<xref linkend=\"fig-browser-for-jesper\"/> below, which is the result of us "
"selecting the Person <literal>Jesper</literal>, you can see an indication of "
"that in the bottom of the window. On the lower right side of <xref linkend="
"\"fig-browser-for-jesper\"/>, you will see that the number of matching "
"images and videos has gone down from 25 to 13, while the total number of "
"images stayed the same."
msgstr ""
"Brskalnik je zdaj poln oseb, ki ste jih določili za svoje slike in "
"videoposnetke <footnote><para>Morda boste opazili, da ima element "
"<literal>Hišni ljubljenčki</literal> posebno ikono. Za podrobnosti o tem "
"glejte <xref linkend=\"sec-specifying-categories\"/>.</para></footnote>, če "
"izberete osebo, se boste vrnili v prvotno stanje brskalnika. Tokrat pa smo "
"<emphasis>v obsegu</emphasis> izbrane osebe. To pomeni, da prikazujemo le "
"informacije o slikah in videoposnetkih, ki vsebujejo to osebo. Glejte <xref "
"linkend=\"fig-browser-for-jesper\"/> spodaj, kar je posledica izbire osebe "
"<literal>Jesper</literal>, kar lahko vidite na dnu okna. V spodnjem desnem "
"kotu <xref linkend=\"fig-browser-for-jesper\"/> boste videli, da se je "
"število ujemajočih se slik in videoposnetkov zmanjšalo s 25 na 13, medtem ko "
"je skupno število slik ostalo enako."

#. Tag: para
#: browsing.docbook:51
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that if there are only a few images in the scope, &kphotoalbum; will "
"directly go to the thumbnail viewer (see <xref linkend=\"chp-thumbnail-view"
"\"/>). You can configure this behaviour in the thumbnail viewer settings "
"(see <xref linkend=\"opt-thumbnails\"/>)."
msgstr ""
"Upoštevajte, da če je v obsegu le nekaj slik, bo &kphotoalbum; neposredno "
"prešel v pregledovalnik sličic (glejte <xref linkend=\"chp-thumbnail-view\"/"
">). To vedenje lahko konfigurirate v nastavitvah pregledovalnika sličic "
"(glejte <xref linkend=\"opt-thumbnails\"/>)."

#. Tag: title
#: browsing.docbook:56
#, no-c-format
msgid "Browser limited to the scope of the person <literal>Jesper</literal>"
msgstr "Brskalnik je omejen na obseg osebe <literal>Jesper</literal>"

#. Tag: para
#: browsing.docbook:65
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If we now continue selecting a new person, then we will get to the images "
"containing both people. Continuing that way you can narrow the set of images "
"that you have in mind down to a few images from a set of thousands."
msgstr ""
"Če zdaj nadaljujemo z izbiro nove osebe, bomo prišli do slik, ki vsebujejo "
"obe osebi. Če nadaljujete tako, lahko zožite nabor slik, ki jih imate v "
"mislih, na nekaj slik iz nabora tisočev."

#. Tag: para
#: browsing.docbook:70
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you are done limiting the scope of images, you may select the "
"<guilabel>View Thumbnails</guilabel> icon, to see exactly those images "
"matching your current scope."
msgstr ""
"Ko končate z omejevanjem obsega slik, lahko izberete ikono <guilabel>Ogled "
"sličic</guilabel>, da si ogledate točno tiste slike, ki ustrezajo vašemu "
"trenutnemu obsegu."

#. Tag: title
#: browsing.docbook:82
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding Preview Images to the Browser"
msgstr "Dodajanje predoglednih slik v brskalnik"

#. Tag: para
#: browsing.docbook:83
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Looking at <xref linkend=\"fig-browser-for-persons\"/> you will see that "
"each person has the same icon in front of his name. &kphotoalbum; is "
"actually capable of showing a preview image for each individual person "
"<footnote><para>This of course also applies to places, keywords, and other "
"categories you have defined yourself.</para></footnote> as can be seen in "
"<xref linkend=\"fig-imagesForPersons\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Če pogledate <xref linkend=\"fig-browser-for-persons\"/>, boste videli, da "
"ima vsaka oseba isto ikono pred svojim imenom. &kphotoalbum; dejansko lahko "
"prikaže predogled slike za vsako posamezno osebo <footnote><para>To seveda "
"velja tudi za kraje, ključne besede in druge kategorije, ki ste jih določili "
"sami.</para></footnote> kot je razvidno iz <xref linkend=\"fig-"
"imagesForPersons\"/>."

#. Tag: title
#: browsing.docbook:91
#, no-c-format
msgid "Images for each Individual Person"
msgstr "Slike za vsako posamezno osebo"

#. Tag: para
#: browsing.docbook:99
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To show images along with the names, choose the tool button to the very "
"right of the toolbar, that will bring up a popup menu, where you can chose "
"which view you want to use for the given category. Notice views must be "
"configured for each category - that way you may for example use an icon view "
"for people, but a plain list view for keywords (in case you can't come up "
"with good images for your keywords)."
msgstr ""
"Če želite prikazati slike skupaj z imeni, izberite orodni gumb na desni "
"strani orodne vrstice, ki bo prikazal pojavni meni, kjer lahko izberete, "
"kateri pogled želite uporabiti za dano kategorijo. Poglede obvestil je treba "
"konfigurirati za vsako kategorijo - tako lahko na primer uporabite pogled "
"ikon za ljudi, vendar navaden pogled seznama za ključne besede (če ne morete "
"najti dobrih slik za svoje ključne besede)."

#. Tag: para
#: browsing.docbook:108
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is, however, your job to tell it which images to use for each individual "
"person. To do so, you must open the viewer (see <xref linkend=\"chp-viewer\"/"
">), and from the context menu choose <guimenuitem>Show Category Editor</"
"guimenuitem>, this will bring up the category editor which can be seen in "
"<xref linkend=\"fig-categoryEditor\"/>. In the category editor you choose "
"the image for the given person. In the viewer it is possible to zoom to part "
"of the image, and that way crop what part should be shown."
msgstr ""
"Vaša naloga pa je, da poveste, katere slike naj uporabi za vsako posamezno "
"osebo. Če želite to narediti, morate odpreti pregledovalnik (glejte <xref "
"linkend=\"chp-viewer\"/>) in v priročnem meniju izbrati <guimenuitem>Pokaži "
"urejevalnik kategorij</guimenuitem>, s tem se prikaže urejevalnik kategorij, "
"ki lahko videti v <xref linkend=\"fig-categoryEditor\"/>. V urejevalniku "
"kategorij izberete sliko za dano osebo. V pregledovalniku je možno povečati "
"del slike in na ta način obrezati, kateri del naj bo prikazan."

#. Tag: title
#: browsing.docbook:118
#, no-c-format
msgid "Category Editor"
msgstr "Urejevalnik kategorij"

#. Tag: title
#: browsing.docbook:139
#, no-c-format
msgid "General image searches"
msgstr "Splošna iskanja slik"

#. Tag: para
#: browsing.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you chose the <guilabel>Search</guilabel> item in the browser, you will "
"get to a dialog with great resemblance to the dialog you used for setting "
"properties of your images. You can see this dialog in <xref linkend=\"fig-"
"search\"/> below."
msgstr ""
"Če v brskalniku izberete element <guilabel>Iskanje</guilabel>, se vam "
"prikaže pogovorno okno, ki je zelo podobno pogovornemu oknu, ki ste ga "
"uporabili za nastavitev lastnosti vaših slik. To pogovorno okno si lahko "
"ogledate v <xref linkend=\"fig-search\"/> spodaj."

#. Tag: title
#: browsing.docbook:146
#, no-c-format
msgid "Search dialog"
msgstr "Pogovorno okno iskanja"

#. Tag: para
#: browsing.docbook:154
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you type a string in the label or description field, then that text will "
"be searched for using substring searches. Likewise you can also specify a "
"date to search for, either as part of a date, say 1971, or as a complete "
"date. You may also specify date ranges, like 1971-1980."
msgstr ""
"Če vnesete niz v polje za oznako ali opis, bo to besedilo poiskano z "
"iskanjem po podnizu. Podobno lahko določite tudi datum za iskanje, bodisi "
"kot del datuma, recimo 1971, bodisi kot celoten datum. Določite lahko tudi "
"časovna obdobja, na primer 1971–1980."

#. Tag: para
#: browsing.docbook:159
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The options item allows a very limited form of writing an expression, as you "
"can see in the example in <xref linkend=\"fig-search\"/>. Here we search for "
"images with <literal>Jesper</literal>, but without <literal>Anne Helene</"
"literal>."
msgstr ""
"Postavka možnosti omogoča zelo omejeno obliko pisanja izraza, kot lahko "
"vidite v primeru v <xref linkend=\"fig-search\"/>. Tukaj iščemo slike z "
"<literal>Jesper</literal>, vendar brez <literal>Anne Helene</literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: browsing.docbook:164
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The allowed operations are &amp; (meaning: and), | (meaning: or), and ! "
"(meaning: not)."
msgstr ""
"Dovoljene operacije so &amp; (kar pomeni: in), | (kar pomeni: ali), in ! "
"(kar pomeni: ne)."

#~ msgid "Browser when images and videos have been annotated"
#~ msgstr "Brskalnik, ko so slike in videoposnetki označeni"
